title: Yoma Hotel
user_reviews: [{"Name":"Richard Zin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUst7w1FOy3Avz5Ozmf33nC0QZpnqBSLGSAWZ2rAN-eALEededr=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I stayed this particular hotel in 2014 (9 years ago).  Room is reasonable and service is average.  Location is great!  Even they provide free breakfast; you don't need it.  Lucky Seven Food Court is just next door and every favorite foods are available.  Just walking distance to 8th Mile Junction; hence all street foods are easily available.  Room price is pretty reasonable when I was there; only Ks20,000 per night.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Krupananda G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QdCjMUwIiBikRhCLHgN_0vyGAo1GvT8DEukiKQb1ujC_eFsFjYrQ0OvLoSxPtqmCdgvFA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"The place was clean. Away from city. Little pricey. There is not much disturbance. Taxis are available easily. Breakfast shall be served in the room. Stayed six nights - got two slices of bread, butter and jam, two eggs half boiled, two pieces of sausage, two bananas and coffee every morning -  no change. Room service was good. I recommend this hotel whole heartedly.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Pam W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qd0Gzx7-o-W0qn7F-oHhorx-ann6UFYRniBmE7Ar1MhRFtO-x6vY7U2LNCPC1lcQidkpw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"We stayed there twice and had good experiences both time.  There is purified water---both hot and cold in  the hallway for free.  The dining room is on the top floor--somewhat of a climb--I think 4th floor, but is nice. Service in dining room is slow, but reasonably tasty and doesn't make you sick.  Our air conditioner died and they had no problems moving us to another room.  Internet is a real challenge--one must go downstairs to what looks like an office area on the side of the hotel.  It has a door and small porch out to the parking area.  We walked down several blocks to the Golden Duck which was always busy and had good food that didn't make us sick.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Michael H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qf66pF81jsVXBxevYxxL5FsdlDsKAngAUpJVE-hAwai1rl8J0QnYqktKV3UGdpbmNlc_A=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I was very easy for us to make a reservation at this hotel via email. ¬†The staff was very responsive. ¬†The bed was a foam mattress, like a very soft tempurpedic, which was surprisingly comfortable. ¬†The location is on the eastern side of downtown Yangon, and it was an easy walk to the man downtown area. ¬†The staff was very helpful in getting us reservations in Mandalay. ¬†It was one of the best hotel staff we experienced while in the country. ¬†They had a good breakfast which they brought to your room. ¬† Wifi was excellent.||||Try to get a room on a lower floor as there's no elevator. ¬†Also, our room didn't have any windows but it wasn't an issue.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Joyce P","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qdx0CtChWdL4amzhVtedU6JgNzs3A9KzPS8K998c7-u-mDeTb-7WQwuTD-PPX6BcVA5wg=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"This is my first time in Myanmar. I didn't know what to expect but I must say I was pleasantly surprised that the stay at Yoma Hotel was actually quite comfortable. The twin room my friend and I stayed in was of a good size and I especially like the fact that it's clean. ||||Just one disturbing thing though. One morning, when I was bathing half way, brown water flowed out of the shower head. I totally freaked out! Thank God, it was just for a while and clean water came back. ||||The staff are friendly and helpful. The hotel is near to the airport and is especially helpful for those who are on early flights. It's easy to get a cab to anywhere so no issue. Good basic hotel.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"JENICE T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qdx0CtChWdL4amzhVtedU6JgNzs3A9KzPS8K998c7-u-mDeTb-7WQwuTD-PPX6BcVA5wg=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Pls note that this is hotel Yoma, the one near to airport, not the other one in town centre. ||||We initially booked a straight 9 nights stay via email, but later on we then knew that our families in Yangon had made certain arrangement for us to go Taunggyi and Inle lake, and we had to stay only two nights and then cancel the rest of the nights for the trip. The hotel staff was able to accommodate our request, and even agreed to reserve for us a room after we came back from our trip. They were very helpful.||||When I first booked the hotel, I was thinking that there will be nothing to amazed me, to my surprise, the stay was very comfortable and nice. Hotel staffs were very helpful and friendly, although some of them have some communication problem(restaurant staff did not really understand the requirement from guests), but overall was a pleasant stay. We arrived with empty stomache and were eagering looking for food, so we ate at the hotel restaurant. Not much variety, but surprisingly, the fried beehoon and rice were delicious. I had ordered one room service one day, it was fish and chips, and it was tasty too, although the fish they used had lots of bones, but basically the taste was yummy!||||Location wise, the hotel is near to the airport, and the hotel provide free transfer to and fro airport. That was very nice, and, the hotel is located near a famous food court, just next to it. Food was okay there but many people came to eat in the morning and noon. Most happy is that, the hotel is also near to the famous Mohingha shop, Tin Tin Aye, just walking distance. And also many other eateries too. ||||Overall this is not a bad choice, if you want somewhere that is not so expensive, and not so busy like in town centre, and with the improved transport system(lots of taxis and if you know which bus to take) in Yangon, you are able to go anywhere you like. Hotel Yoma will be one of my choices for my next visit to yangon again!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Nicola E","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeNj0UTN0yIrCGyJ0JhWwDODOg5QjAH0gdfB9Ji-oFl0zWFI-YVmhNAr-FGLycdpIjFmw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I stayed in three different rooms on three different trips to Yangon over my holiday. ||The rooms with no outside windows were large, comfortable and well-equipped. The room with outside windows was a bit smaller, but was very comfy with a great view over the railway and the mosque. ||||The rooms were all very clean and well-equipped, with everything functioning. ||||The staff were incredibly friendly, competent and helpful. ||||There are loads of great restaurants, bars and shops on the couple of blocks around this hotel and it is also relatively easy to walk around to some sites such as Sule or Botataung if you don't mind walking and enjoy wandering at a leisurely pace taking photos and stopping in tea shops. ||||I stayed in this hotel because it was near a friend's house, but I would recommend it to anyone as it was so friendly and well-organised. ||||Breakfast in bed at a time of your choosing was also a plus!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Isabel W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfsnvlNO8mgROWsxiGYBmc-FMApm47le01WrNgEyYNYqUPw1j7nx-COV-HLlhXF8VUXQQ=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Normal rooms were $50 but we took a $35 room which had an incredibly low ceiling, touched my head and I am 5ft 9! A bit like a hobbit room but was very clean with fridge and tv, aircon and water. Bathroom was downstairs from the room but not shared. No noise and comfortable. Bit of a walk to anywhere but we didn't mind. Can't comment on breakfast as we left early for a flight with a standard crappy breakfast box. They did kindly give us coffee before we left through (unusual for Myanmar) and there was good free wifi.","Images":null,"When":""}]

title: Royal Tian Li

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Moe Myint Mg Mg","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWVVFX1-cyhnesb7-q-Qp_1TMMvmYE6-EKxxf6J-sEG5KvvzD1b=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I recently stayed at Royal Tian Li, and my experience was extremely disappointing from start to finish.

1. Poor Communication and Lack of Knowledge:
When I called the hotel‚Äôs operator staff to inquire about a promotion I saw on their Facebook page, they were completely clueless. They acted like they weren‚Äôt even part of the hotel staff and had no knowledge of the promotion or anything related to the hotel. It was incredibly frustrating and unprofessional.

2. Unwelcoming Reception:
Upon checking in, I found the receptionists to be just as unhelpful and lazy as the operator staff. They were unwelcoming and didn‚Äôt provide any information about the hotel, such as breakfast timings or amenities. It felt like they couldn‚Äôt care less about their guests.

3. Horrible Room Conditions:
The room was absolutely appalling. It smelled awful, and the duvet cover was full of stains. It was clear that cleanliness and guest comfort are not priorities at this hotel.

4. Embarrassing Incident at the Pool:
While my girlfriend and I were at the pool, a waiter invited us to enjoy a free BBQ. However, when I asked about the timings, a senior cashier rudely informed us that it was a staff party. This was an incredibly embarrassing and awkward moment. It‚Äôs shocking that the staff doesn‚Äôt even know their own guests and fail to communicate properly among themselves.

5. Pathetic Breakfast:
The breakfast was a joke. There was only fried rice and bread available, yet they have the audacity to call it a ‚Äúluxury hotel‚Äôs buffet.‚Äù It was far from it. They should just call it √† la carte and be done with it.

Overall, my stay at Royal Tian Li was a nightmare. The staff is unprofessional and untrained, the rooms are dirty, and the amenities are far below any acceptable standard. I would not recommend this hotel to anyone.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kelly C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QdCjMUwIiBikRhCLHgN_0vyGAo1GvT8DEukiKQb1ujC_eFsFjYrQ0OvLoSxPtqmCdgvFA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"This hotel is perfect for a staycation. Staff were all extremely attentive, and the breakfast buffet had plenty of choice, including freshly cooked omelettes on demand. Although its not in the city centre, its only 2 minutes walk to the train station and you can get to the city by train for 20 cents(or all the way round the city - 3 hours), and see lots of local life on the way. Taxis to/from the city are 4-5 dollars. Thomas, the owner, was very helpful booking us cheap overnight bus tickets to Mandalay when we couldn't do so because of high demand after the full moon festival. title: Hotel Kamarkyi
descriptions: Warmly decorated rooms in an unpretentious hotel offering a restaurant & a fitness center.
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Win Mar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUY81owTtmMzrjereg1c86bHiG8bHe_JbLoVzGe45YGUQOHyE8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Breakfast is not bad and you can watch morning views on the rooftop. It's cool üòé. Service is not bad and the room is not bad. But water is strange. The location is very good and easy to get there.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Simon Hehe","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUj7zKdHHDw9y-DOnzqO3zzeZvCxWgVNgrGR0NJs-H1h7fJhgI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Food-the variety was underwhelming to say the least and it was decent at best.Quite the disappointment I suppose.

Facilities-Just the gym, no spa, and no nothing. The gym is quite facilitied but the machines are broken(running machines) which is quite sad considering the fact that that was the selling point of the gym tbh. But there certainly is one for each type of exercise-lats, triceps, biceps, legs, and arms. But there is only about one for each which ain't that much but it gets the job done.

Rooms-we didn't get those typa "expensive and luxurious" rooms and got a family room and a superior double bed. The family room was quite capacious but the superior one was quite small, might be due to the price but it's to be expected.

Service-A lil over average ova. The speed is consistent and when we ordered some snacks from the hotel, both time, the order were sent within 20min and the taste was restruant type quality and the prices were quite inexpensive considering the tax and service fees that were added ova.

Conclusion-A great hotel, was great for the price. View was somewhat great with the river side view but am not a photo takin typa guy so what would I know:3 the services werent bad. Would recommend if you're in the area and just want to get the night over with. But if you want to get a feel of luxury and comfort, this place does offer some but there are many places that are better but this is one of the best 3-stars hotel imo{i don't rlly lodge in 3 stars but from what I've seen, this is by far the best one yet, tho ion understand why there ain't a spa or onsen:(}

Ova? Would recommend if u be in a hurry.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Nyein Su San","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK26icXTn8zKGGw63se8qYK3x72r3wWpnBhFLhQVT1zZ-O81Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"For the first day, they take extra charges 10000 MMK for children under 10.

There was also no construction when I was there. My room is huge (and ceiling high), the television is so far away (8-10m) from my bed I have problem seeing the details. In contrast my hotel room in the city centre was so small that the TV is mounted like 80cm from the bed and they have to put it near the ceiling to increase the distance. The rooms are very well furnished (best value for money IMHO) and bigger than the family room that I had booked at the nearby Crystal Palace Hotel. It is a modern hotel with card entry. If you stay at the hotel you get a 20% discount at the Spa and the ONLY treatment I would recommend is the traditional massage at 10,000 kyat before discount. The Monalisa Restaurant (Level 1) is actually excellent and reasonably priced that I ended having dinner there every night. The breakfast is not excellent but quite good. There is actually an omelette counter so you can have you eggs done in any way but I did not see any eggs swimming in grease.||While the Wifi is not great, the signal is relatively strong and it is actually better than most hotels in Myanmar. Internet speed is not fast in the whole country and may break off.||Having stayed at various locations in Yangon, I can say this hotel is very centrally located. You can walk to visit Chauk Htat Gyi and Nga Htat Gyi Pagodas and be back within 2 hours without rushing. Shwedagon is also within walking distance.Downtown and Kandawgyi Lake are also not far away.  ||The best thing about this hotel is the hot water. You get very hot water very fast, better than some 5 star hotels.||Try not to venture to the basement as it is a "Love Tunnel" mostly for the local businessmen. The hotel staff is helpful, friendly and professional. Highly recommended, it is unbeatable at the price I paid. The only negative about this hotel is that there are no shops, shopping centres or amenities nearby. There is a diesel generator planted at the entrance of the hotel so any electrical outages are very short.","Images":null,"When":""}]

title: Guest Care Hotel
user_reviews: [{"Name":"Wolfgang B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QcKrc8e2JnTu8c7_hmoZKea10RMTDbKaR4QZbjFBwR43DXTBpqzkG_SGZrLD47rFdkvjQ=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Stayed there in March and April at the beginning and the end of my trip across Myanmar. Room could need a make up but was clean and spacy.||Breakfast is served at Cafe Circles which is next to the hotel, a very nice restaurant where they serve good food. I asked for Mohinga, the typical Burmese fish soup, they organized it for me and I liked it very much.||Good Wifi !||From the hotel it¬¥s only a 10 minutes walk to the amazing Shwedagon Pagoda. Some good dining opportunities close to the hotel.||Staff very friendly and helpful.||Would come back if again in Yangon.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jetpiloteyes","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qdx0CtChWdL4amzhVtedU6JgNzs3A9KzPS8K998c7-u-mDeTb-7WQwuTD-PPX6BcVA5wg=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"The Guest Care lets itself down with some pretty unnecessary shortcomings. The best thing about the Hotel are the cheerful, friendly, helpful staff, who deserve credit. The rooms are a bit tired and decorated in a random way, as if they just used whatever was to hand. Views vary quite considerably, from decent ones into a (admittedly decrepit) garden, to boring ones over roofs and roads. Rooms smelt musty, and some had visible mould growing (in the dry season), but this is not unusual in Yangon. Design is a bit illogical - in the room I was in the TV was placed in a position where it was almost impossible to watch it! The water pressure in the shower is only just sufficient and water temperature tends to swing between scalding and freezing at random. They do not advertise laundry and minibar costs in any of the rooms, which seems to me due to either carelessness or an underhand attempt to fleece unwary customers. So, check the prices with reception before use either as they are not cheap! There is no internet provided in the rooms, which puts them behind competitors in this price range. I sense this is because they want to encourage guests to hang out at the Coffee Circles restaurant which is next door and owned by the same people I assume. The free breakfast are also served at Coffee Circles and is a monotonous two eggs, two pretty revolting and rubber little frankfurter style sausages, deep fried, a piece of polystyrene masquerading as toast and a pot of strong (but rarely) hot coffee. As someone has mentioned before, 'long-stay' guests can get Myanmar breakfast options - mohinga, ouq-nouq khao swe (noodles with chicken), and pauq-si (dumpling) with a spring roll. As the 'Western' set breakfast is so monotonous, I don't know why they don't just offer this option to all guests as standard. Even if you are not 'long stay', worth lobbying for this option, as it gets hard to eat the 'Western' breakfast after a couple of days. The wireless connection at Coffee Circles is also pretty shaky and the food is pretty uninspiring. Overall, I don't think this hotel offers good value for money. It is well-positioned and convenient, but my sense is that it is being milked as a cash cow by the owners who don't seem to be very interested in making it a good experience for guests, but rather providing the bare minimum in order to extract the maximum amount of cash out of them. To reiterate, the exception to the rule are the staff, whose genuinely friendly attitudes make the whole experience a lot better than it would otherwise be. Due to the supply/demand imbalance created by the recent influx of tourists and development workers, Yangon hotels are notoriously bad value for money. I think that the Guest Care will be able to get away with offering this very mediocre experience for a couple more years, but then with supply catching up with demand, they will start to seriously fall behind if they don't raise their game of lower their prices significantly. As it is, there are better options available for the money.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Germana B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QdHDxxyBDO6igPA51sqxYAI1TTeuGvapT1sWSCJfPSgzOZltNlMhWmUDpj2A3v7zAw89g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I have been living and travelling in Thailand in the last 4 years and this was my first time in Yangon for a business trip. We chose the hotel because it was near our meeting venue and also it is very central. Not knowing anything about burmese standard, the hotel looks like it was kind of nice 20 years ago and never got any renovation since. The room was not small but very old, the toilet not extremely clean with the shower curtain showing (many) signs of needing a change. No internet in the room and no hot water. The air con was old but working ok. The breakfast was nothing special. Only very nice thing, I could see the top of Shwedagon Pagoda from my room. Overall, considering that we paid 70USD per night, I think it is overpriced.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Happy T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QdcKHisBXAOJmIugCgnKbcAscQkQI1t40WdQAMXk1g3ttzWj18FtKnHxNeSUm5OfHPMtQ=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"To be honest,  it is years ago that I have visited this hotel.  Nevertheless, I wish to share that the hotel is in a good location to visit, the Shwedagon Pagoda, a MUST see when you are in Yangon. I have visited the hotel for busines; I have stayed there over 3 weeks. The personnel is friendly and helpfull, the rooms are very limited, but for the price we paid, more than acceptable. Breakfast was nice with hot soul and fresh fruit, really good to \"kick-start\" your day. All in all a good experience.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Melanie R","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qf66pF81jsVXBxevYxxL5FsdlDsKAngAUpJVE-hAwai1rl8J0QnYqktKV3UGdpbmNlc_A=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I stayed here for about 4 weeks in all, on a work trip. The staff were lovely and always ready to help, which is its best feature along with the location, in the heart of an area with lots of dining options and near Shwedagon Pagoda - of which you will get good views from the upper rooms. Carpets are grimy and worn, but otherwise the room was always kept clean.  Everything is rather worn around the edges, but beds were good and I was perfectly comfortable.  Breakfast at Coffee Circles is monotonous - and they forgot to mention that there is more than one boring option if you are a \"long stay guest\". Be sure to enquire about this, since you can get mohinga and other set breakfasts. Staff there are also very sweet. Oh yeah, the Internet (sourced from Coffee Circles) was extremely unreliable, they need to upgrade their equipment.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Pamela B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qd0Gzx7-o-W0qn7F-oHhorx-ann6UFYRniBmE7Ar1MhRFtO-x6vY7U2LNCPC1lcQidkpw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"My boyfriend and I made the mistake of not booking any hotels/guest houses until we actually got to Myanmar.. With Internet access being hard to come by we resorted to our lonely planet book as reference for all of our stay throughout Myanmar. We chose Guest Care Hotel because Lonely Planet quoted the price as $20-22/room (we wanted a cheaper place to stay because we ended up spending quite a bit more through out our trip than we had expected). When we got to the hotel after a long day of travel we ended up paying $65 (the first price they quoted us was $70, after he called his boss he said he could bring his price down to $65, but no lower) for the most basic room that they had. The room was ok, not awful but definitely nothing fancy. For the price we paid we did not feel the room was worth it. If possible, book before you arrive Myanmar.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Travellingtoes","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeCck1CfANpZm9bBk3PHtP97Kh9k25HZfvq9yAWlN3BaIyjSHUPEfWkhAJmuYiJsH-_6g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"After having checked twice that my taxi on arrival was booked, there was a no show as I arrived in Yangon at midnight. Breakfast is included in the nearby coffee house, which adds to the stay , although this will not be the best breakfast you will ever have!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"the_lofty_attic","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeqQESQs2CRf2VRyln1Raq0k2FSdB19mGKme5Xh6nHXcs2V7pTrOayJAdxC-qWdu9VyTA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"And that's being next to circles cafe which has fairly decent food.||The hotel itself is dingy and very basic. My room was not clean and not easy to lock from the inside. The worst part was the awful foam mattress leading to a rather poor night's sleep - for $60 a night it should be better.","Images":null,"When":""}]

Service and rooms are needed to improve in future.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"michele f","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QftlnsLB8VReEIa8q3x-FUIWL9jAVnw9OiPzFml0xLx7k1DporKgZdMXGALflbNzntF3w=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"The location of this hotel is convenient, near the shewdagon pagoda, near the park and bus stop (if you really understand how it works !). the hotel is clean, the rooms are big enough, free wifi and breakfast is quite good. We stayed there for a week since it was booked by the organisation but it's not the type of hotel you want to stay except for sleeping at night. || the windows were overlooking the pagoda and at night it was really beautiful. 100 meters from the hotel there is a nice bar sharky's with fresh croissants and good coffee.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Nay Linn","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXq3EohvIHuCR_P_0s1Gfzy0bc-BaXef-BwLwgYFZaR8f6MeuaR=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Very bad service. You can choose the better hotel than this with such price and service.
I had a bad experience. I have been outside the whole afternoon and came back at 7pm. I reminded the reception to clean my room when i left the room key before I go outside. After i came back, my room was still the same.
I called the reception immediately and reception cant respond me well and they were acting to blame on each staff. Such a bad responsibility. A few mins later, i have to sit outside waiting for their cleaning time. Hotel is quite rather old and interior painting are shedding off at some areas inside the room. I would definitely not to stay there again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMR9Mc62ViuHWlJUIW9wQ7H7BSbpwwFYA-mfEXl&fid=0x0:0x5c3446d28fab20dd"],"When":"2018-11-24"},{"Name":"Anna T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfjHmZg8gr7jpDgKhrh5KsR_Mq7L6pkVedvpKQz-f3LMiOd3OjI90CK4uLtF3wE59zZgA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"The hotel proudly bares its one-star rating on a plaque at the front desk. It is a budget hotel, often used by local organisations to host out-of-towners who are attending workshops or training programs.  Overall it was clean enough and somewhere to lay your head at night, but no real atmosphere and I did not feel like spending any time at the hotel (in my room or elsewhere).  There are other hotels nearby that are better value.||||The room was clean, with a kettle and fridge, wifi in the rooms was ok (I found I could stream audio late at night).  The staff were reasonably friendly.  ||||I had a room on one side of the hotel and could see Shewdagon Pagoda if I strained my neck out the window.  It was not too noisy - rooms at the front might be louder.  We lost power several times, although this is par for the course in many parts of Yangon.||||The restaurant is in the basement, food is ok, but nothing special.  Breakfast was actually not bad, I thought the Burmese food was quite tasty and there was always fresh fruit.  ||||I just found myself desperate for better light (rooms quite dark, basement restaurant has no windows) or somewhere to sit (the lobby is also in the basement).  The elevator has very limited capacity and frequently is overloaded (e.g. some guests have to wait).","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Aung Myo H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfjHmZg8gr7jpDgKhrh5KsR_Mq7L6pkVedvpKQz-f3LMiOd3OjI90CK4uLtF3wE59zZgA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Location is very convenient and located in downtown yangon. Very close to Shwedagon Pagoda. Hotel rooms are spacious and air conditioning present. Bathrooms are also clean and well spaced. Breakfast is just ordinary. Price is neither cheap nor expensive. Hotel staff are not very friendly but helpful. Whatever, because of its location, a nice place to stay at night.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"mrvalte","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QftlnsLB8VReEIa8q3x-FUIWL9jAVnw9OiPzFml0xLx7k1DporKgZdMXGALflbNzntF3w=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I was booked in the said hotel by an organization that sponsored my trip late last year. The hotel is old and stuffy (the lobby smelled of old, unwashed carpet), though it is conveniently located and has basic amenities that should suit a budget traveler: airconditioning, free wifi, free breakfast -- the hotel restaurant offers good food -- but no hot shower, at least in my room. The staff were helpful, too. If all you need is a place to deposit your luggage while you're out on business, Sweet Hotel will do.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Toe Myint Naing","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWeHlz813KIwpVX4yxwHQEKOF1ln9mc0BYv-iePhvDIC3P7ckEq=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"**Room Standard is equal to a motel.
Broken toilet
Weak wifi
Unsure how many cctv there, can't even catch a mobile data connection.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Charlene M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeYuXGoFc9HnT35lAJ46cKDIsHY7nNIKUKz_f8yINNlqyrU48jCx-4ctPzihRKgde030w=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"This is a very basic hotel that has what you need and a little more.  Clean rooms, clean linens, functional AC, small refrigerator, and comfortable beds.  ||Staff is very helpful with directions, taxis, and shopping questions.||Breakfast each morning is relatively unchanging, but adequate to fill you up, esp if you like rice, noodles, and fresh fruit.||It is one of the closest hotels to the Shwe Dagon Pagoda, only a 10 minute walk up the hill to the pagoda AND some great new restaurants right across the street from the pagoda.||Internet is free and available in the rooms, but their connection speed is very slow.  Email OK, but forget streaming.  Downloading a movie took all night.","Images":null,"When":""}]
